What's this?

256
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,820
You had class duty today, Yakuin-kun?

257
00:13:26,220 --> 00:13:29,100
The guy who does asked me to take the morning shift because he had stuff to do.

258
00:13:30,830 --> 00:13:32,680
I see. Perfect timing.

259
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:36,320
Come to the faculty office with Watanabe-kun after school today.

260
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,080
What?

261
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:39,800
Make sure both husband and wife come.

262
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,740
Okay, I will.

263
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:56,690
It must be going well between Shiori and Tenjin.

264
00:13:56,990 --> 00:13:58,900
I haven't been there yet.

265
00:13:56,990 --> 00:14:01,210
I thought that if I acted like this, she might worry about me and say something,

266
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:03,180
Really? Then let's go. I just know you'll like it.

267
00:14:01,210 --> 00:14:01,940
but she hasn't.

268
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:05,460
And just thinking that way shows how gloomy I am, right?
I'd love to go!

269
00:14:04,970 --> 00:14:06,950
Okay, it's settled, then!
That back there was probably...

270
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,080
Hey!

271
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:10,180
What is it, Shiori?

272
00:14:10,660 --> 00:14:12,950
You don't mind, do you? We're married, after all!

273
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:15,810
It's fine with me, but what about him?

274
00:14:15,810 --> 00:14:17,210
You mean Jiro-kun?

275
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:20,540
It's no problem at all! He's just an old friend.

276
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:23,630
You're so cool, and you help me move forward.

277
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,630
My own imaginings are making me cry.

278
00:14:33,180 --> 00:14:36,090
It's raining? I don't have an umbrella.

279
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:39,220
Don't worry. I have one.

280
00:14:39,220 --> 00:14:41,770
I have to share an umbrella with you?

281
00:14:41,770 --> 00:14:43,150
No complaining!

282
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:46,650
Man, today was just another dull day.

283
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:48,450
I had a good day, though.

284
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:51,420
My free morning gacha pull got me an S-rare card in a school swimsuit costume.

285
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:53,020
That's thanks to me, right?

286
00:14:53,020 --> 00:14:54,190
Buy me something.

287
00:14:54,190 --> 00:14:57,410
Can't. I started saving up for Marin-chan today.

288
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:59,360
There it is again. Hashimoto Marin.

289
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,030
Use honorifics for other people's girlfriends!

290
00:15:01,030 --> 00:15:02,170
Marin-san.

291
00:15:02,410 --> 00:15:03,460
Very good.

292
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:08,170
In the story for this event, Marin-chan makes omelet rice for you,

293
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:09,670
and it was so good!

294
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:11,930
The taste of it maxed out my love meter!

295
00:15:11,930 --> 00:15:14,300
"You can't possibly know how a JPEG tastes," you say?

296
00:15:14,590 --> 00:15:17,470
Fool! A JPEG is meant to be savored with the occipital lobe!

297
00:15:17,470 --> 00:15:18,430
Stop for a sec.

298
00:15:18,310 --> 00:15:20,310
Occipital Lobe
Parietal Lobe
Frontal Lobe
Temporal Lobe
By the way, this is the part I mean.

299
00:15:20,310 --> 00:15:23,020
Move! You're in the way!

300
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,430
I might be late today.

301
00:15:26,430 --> 00:15:28,040
Okay... Why?

302
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:30,480
I'm going to karaoke, and Minami-kun is coming!

303
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:32,340
Oh, is that so?

304
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:33,450
Later!

305
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:37,870
Wait! Wait, Watanabe.

306
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:38,920
What is it?

307
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:42,160
I just remembered. The teacher said we need to go to the faculty office.

308
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:43,460
It's about the practical.

309
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:46,300
Oh... I guess we have no choice, then.

310
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:48,750
Take care of it solo, 'kay?

311
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:50,260
Hey!

312
00:15:50,660 --> 00:15:52,530
You've gotta be kidding me!

313
00:15:52,530 --> 00:15:54,640
This really was the worst day ever.

314
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:56,450
To hell with that!

315
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:58,100
Your childhood friend is the pure, sweet type,

316
00:15:58,100 --> 00:15:59,470
and your mock wife is a hot gyaru?!

317
00:15:59,470 --> 00:16:01,140
You've got a flower in each hand!

318
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:02,960
Are you the hero of a harem anime or something?!

319
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:03,770
Oh, shut up.

320
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:07,740
I could live on the carbon dioxide Akari-chan exhales, personally.

321
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:10,880
If anything, I am carbon dioxide itself.

322
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:11,650
Huh?

323
00:16:11,650 --> 00:16:13,910
Meaning no one needs me.

324
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:16,160
Faculty Office
No, it's absolutely necessary.

325
00:16:16,930 --> 00:16:20,320
The marriage practical isn't playing at being friends. It's coursework.

326
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,160
It's necessary for graduation.

327
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:28,670
71st
Kasugahara Kyo
Sangamori Hatsune
72nd
Yakuin Jiro
Watanabe Akari
Kaizuka Yoshitake
Nakahara Miyako

328
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:26,080
Your score hasn't gone up or down for a week. It's stayed at zero.

329
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,670
At this rate, you really won't be able to graduate.

330
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:32,920
Talk things over with Watanabe-san so that you can strive to be a happily married couple.

331
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,180
Unlimited Time
Karaoke 30 minutes 100 yen Unlimited Time 1000 yen

332
00:16:35,180 --> 00:16:37,430
Minami-kun, you're super good at this!

333
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:39,750
And your English is so good! I was surprised!

334
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:43,900
Thanks. But there aren't many songs I can sing.

335
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,840
My voice is all hoarse already.

336
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,900
Wanna sing together?

337
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:45,190
Of course you can!
What did you pick, Watanabe?

338
00:16:45,590 --> 00:16:46,670
Go, Akari!

339
00:16:45,590 --> 00:16:48,010
Oh, this is it! Higashino Kana-chan!

340
00:16:48,010 --> 00:16:48,830
Here.

341
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:51,690
Huh? I don't know if I can keep singing.

342
00:16:49,850 --> 00:16:51,690
I've heard you sing before. You're good.

343
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:52,830
Really?

344
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:55,900
Then maybe I'll give it my best this time.

345
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:01,200
This rain just isn't stopping.

346
00:17:01,870 --> 00:17:04,220
It's easy to say to try to be a happily married couple,

347
00:17:04,220 --> 00:17:07,210
but she's probably off having fun with her real love interest.

348
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:12,060
Hey, Akari is tired from singing.

349
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,970
Why don't we go take a little breather in the next room?

350
00:17:16,650 --> 00:17:19,180
What am I thinking?!

351
00:17:20,290 --> 00:17:21,500
There's no helping it.

352
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,940
I'll just deal with getting wet,

353
00:17:22,940 --> 00:17:25,200
buy dinner from a convenience store, and head home.

354
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,690
Oh? You're still here at school?

355
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:31,130
Shio— Sakurazaka?! What are you doing here so late?

356
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:33,190
We had a committee meeting today.

357
00:17:33,190 --> 00:17:34,440
May I sit next to you?

358
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:36,110
S-Sure.

359
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,590
This rain isn't letting up, huh?

360
00:17:41,590 --> 00:17:42,700
Do you have an umbrella?

361
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,460
I forgot it!

362
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:47,710
Jiro has suffered near-fatal damage.

363
00:17:46,610 --> 00:17:47,710
I-I see.

364
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:49,960
Eek!

365
00:17:55,630 --> 00:17:57,220
Oh, I was mistaken.

366
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:59,120
Sorry. I thought there was a bug.

367
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:01,220
Oh, yeah, it's easy to mistake that doodle for a bug.

368
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:05,340
When I got here this morning, there was a huge one.

369
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:06,980
I thought it might've come back.

370
00:18:06,980 --> 00:18:08,040
I'm really sorry.

371
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:09,950
It's fine. I was surprised, that's all.

372
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:12,500
Wait, then was that...

373
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:14,980
Bug!

374
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:18,890
Hey, Sakurazaka...

375
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:19,610
I hate that.
Huh?

376
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:23,240
It makes me feel lonely.

377
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:27,250
I want you to call me "Shiori" like you used to.

378
00:18:29,490 --> 00:18:30,920
Won't you?

379
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,500
Wh-What's going on? What's this mean?

380
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:36,810
I don't really get it, but there's one thing I do know...

381
00:18:36,810 --> 00:18:39,070
This is the time for me to be brave!

382
00:18:40,470 --> 00:18:42,210
Sh-Sh-Shio—

383
00:18:42,210 --> 00:18:43,080
Shiori.

384
00:18:44,530 --> 00:18:46,060
Minami-kun?

385
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:50,390
But I thought you were going to be out late doing karaoke.

386
00:18:52,470 --> 00:18:56,800
I remembered seeing your collapsible umbrella in the entryway.

387
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:57,720
Oh, but...

388
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:01,780
Th-That's great! I'm gonna try waiting a little longer.

389
00:19:01,780 --> 00:19:03,280
You should go on ahead.

390
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,280
But...

391
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:06,600
I'll be fine.

392
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:09,250
See you tomorrow, Sakurazaka.

393
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:12,100
Yeah.

394
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:32,850
Here.

395
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:37,700
What sort of expression is that?

396
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:42,780
Ugh!

397
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:45,870
What's there to enjoy about sharing an umbrella with you?

398
00:19:46,730 --> 00:19:51,370
And why didn't you go off somewhere with Sakurazaka-san so it'd be just the two of you?

399
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:56,250
If you had, I'd be sharing an umbrella with Minami-kun right about now.

400
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:57,670
Sorry.

401
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:01,870
Do you really have any intention of snagging that girl?

402
00:20:02,390 --> 00:20:03,350
Sorry.

403
00:20:05,790 --> 00:20:07,020
Hey!

404
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,640
No giving up!

405
00:20:10,940 --> 00:20:13,900
For both my sake and yours.

406
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:14,880
Understand?

407
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:15,900
Yesh.

408
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:17,340
Very good.

409
00:20:19,730 --> 00:20:22,590
This is probably Watanabe's way of being considerate of me.

410
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:25,550
I really am such a loser.

411
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:26,980
Is the rain starting to let up?

412
00:20:27,390 --> 00:20:28,410
It might be.

413
00:20:28,850 --> 00:20:31,120
Actually, I'm starving.

414
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:33,200
Should we drop by a convenience store for dinner?

415
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:34,660
No.

416
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:38,440
It's fine.

417
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,190
Here you go!

418
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,510
It's real omelet rice!

419
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,160
Looks delicious, doesn't it?

420
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,500
Y-Yeah!

421
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,020
Wait!

422
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,830
You have to move slowly, okay?

423
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:58,860
You can't let it spurt out too quickly.

424
00:20:59,330 --> 00:21:00,730
Oh, not there!

425
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,490
Be a little more gentle...

426
00:21:03,940 --> 00:21:05,740
Yes, that's so good.

427
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:09,490
Love

428
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:14,270
I filled it with my love. Please, enjoy.

429
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:17,820
I-I will, thank you!

430
00:21:19,610 --> 00:21:21,000
It's good!

431
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:23,120
Of course it is!

432
00:21:24,130 --> 00:21:25,480
I'll have some, too.

433
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:26,280
Wait!

434
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:31,720
Here, say "ah."

435
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:37,330
No way. I'm not doing that.

436
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:39,510
C'mon! Just go with it, please!

437
00:21:39,510 --> 00:21:41,650
This is super embarrassing for me!

438
00:21:42,150 --> 00:21:44,150
Damn it. I'm never doing this again.

439
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:53,250
It's delicious! That's my cooking for you!

440
00:22:05,050 --> 00:22:07,970
Really? Marin-san made curry omelet rice for you?

441
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:07,970
Jiro

442
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:10,740
Thanks for the save.

443
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:12,360
Huh? What's that mean?

444
00:22:11,190 --> 00:22:13,720
What was that? Why is...

445
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:13,720
What did I save you from?

446
00:22:14,410 --> 00:22:16,980
...my heart pounding so fast?

447
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:19,560
I don't get it.

448
00:23:50,030 --> 00:23:56,530
Jiro "Every night before taking a bath, Watanabe emerges from her room with an even sexier expression than usual. Why could that be?"

449
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,590
Every night before taking a bath,

450
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:55,480
Watanabe emerges from her room with an even sexier expression than usual.

451
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,530
Why could that be?

452
00:23:56,530 --> 00:23:58,160
Jiro "The mystery was quickly solved."
The mystery was quickly solved.

453
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:00,540
Akari "Unh......... Unh......... Mmm........."

454
00:24:00,540 --> 00:24:02,230
Th-That voice...

455
00:24:00,540 --> 00:24:04,540
Jiro "Th......... That voice......... My body moved of its own accord, despite knowing it was wrong..."

456
00:24:02,230 --> 00:24:04,540
My body moved of its own accord, despite knowing it was wrong...

457
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:08,050
Jiro "Of course that's it! I'm embarrassed at myself for imagining differently!"
Of course that's it! I'm embarrassed at myself for imagining differently!

458
00:24:08,050 --> 00:24:10,050
Next time, "Imagined, but Not Real."
Imagined, but Not Real.

